BLUETONGUE - EUROPE (08): RUSSIA, EU, BTV-14, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
*********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 22 Nov 2012
Source: Official site of Rosselkhoznadzor, Russia's Federal Service for Veterinary and Phytosanitary Surveillance [machine transl, summarised, edited]
http://fsvps.ru/fsvps/news/5591.html


Eugene Nepoklonov, Deputy Head of Rosselkhoznadzor and chief veterinary inspector of Russia, noted [during talks with the CVO of the UK, Nigel Gibben] that the distribution of bluetongue in the EU remains an acute problem.

His particular concern was the detection in Belarus of animals suspected as infected with BTV-8 as well as with the exotic BTV-14. The latter, he said, were suspected to have been imported from Poland and the Baltic States.

Besides this, Rosselkhoznadzor had information on a sick calf in Spain, suspected to be infected by the same BTV-14. Nepoklonov underlined the need for updated information on bluetongue in Europe and expressed particular concern on the widening presence of bluetongue in northern Europe. Previously, that region was regarded as free of the disease due to its climatic conditions, unsuitable for the BTV insect vectors.

--
